whereas.text:
Whereas today, people who are deaf-blind are attending college, participating in social activities,
			 managing their everyday lives and actively engaged in their community
			 through employment and civic activities;

Whereas in 1984, responding to the need for more awareness about the Deaf-Blind community, Congress
			 passed a resolution marking the last week in June as Helen Keller
			 Deaf-Blind Awareness Week;
